RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRANITIANSEVENSIX got put in tight between rivals early then moved back into range from inside, drew closer along the rail then two wide late on the turn, drew alongside BELMONT BILL with a sixteenth to go and got up nearing the wire. BELMONT BILL set the pace under pressure early, cleared on the turn, met the challenge from the winner at the sixteenth pole but could not hold on. NEON LIGHTS (IRE) chased three deep into the turn, remained three wide to the stretch, steered out in the lane and edged MIDNIGHT FURY for the show honors. MIDNIGHT FURY pressed from outside, chased the leader two to three wide outside a rival around the bend, could not re-rally in the drive and lost the show. RAHM shifted in to bumped rival at the start, lacked room behind foe from the three-eighths pole to the five-sixteenths pole, cut the corner into the lane and kept on while unable to threaten. PLAYER B was off slow from outside, raced at the back outside a rival to the turn, went two to three wide around the bend, angled out and could not rally. POP POP'S RIDE broke slow and got bumped back at the start, puled the rider along up the backstretch, traveled along the fence then went between rivals late on the bend, angled out at the top of the lane and failed to menace. CAPTAIN SPARROW away quicky then chased the top pair to the turn, entered the lane two wide and weakened. MOBE TOWN raced in range early then off the pace, went three to four wide wide around the bend and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAMBO raced up close from outside early, bid two wide into the turn, vied three deep at the quarter pole, took over in upper stretch, dueled through the final furlong and gamely prevailed. DESERT RHAPSODY forwardly placed between early then got put in a bit tight to lose ground into the turn, came again and challenged four deep with a quarter mile remaining, dueled outside TAMBO down the lane and was denied. ASIAN MATRIARCH was reluctant to load into the gate, stalked from inside into the turn, launched a rail bid at the quarter pole but got outkicked by the top pair in the final furlong. CARALOVA took control early, pressured by TAMBO into the turn, vied along the rail then between rivals leaving the bend, was overtaken in upper stretch and weakened. SUPER ENTICING chased while climbing a bit early, rounded the bend two to three wide and lacked a rally. SAKURA BLOSSOM steadied behind ASIAN MATRIARCH early then climbed and was guided out, went four then five wide around the turn and failed to menace. UNION HEIRESS climbed early while dropping back under coaxing, took the turn two to three wide and could not make an impact. SELDOVIA chased three wide into the turn, five wide into the stretch and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: NINEELEVENTURBO stalked the pace along the rail, tipped out around the final turn and took aim three wide into the stretch, launched a bid and bumped with inner rival at the three-sixteenths pole, quickly cleared after and drew away under hand urging and coasted in near the wire. EXPLAIN THIS AUDIT chased three wide into the first turn then dropped back to tuck inside, coaxed along leaving the backstretch inching closer, swung out leaving the far turn and finished determinedly but had to settle for second best. SEVEN WONDERS dueled for the lead around the first turn then ceded command, closest in pursuit from the two path in the early, moved up to duel again from outside on the final bend, bumped while taking over at the top of the lane, relinquished the lead shortly after, flattened late but managed to hold the show. KINGMEISTER antsy in the gate, got put in a bit tight early, reserved in the two path after, got blocked at the five-sixteenths pole then again at the quarter pole, angled in around the far turn, steered out in the lane and churned on for a minor award. COWBOY JUSTICE (GB) dueled around the first turn from the rail, cleared first time in the stretch, dueled around the final bend, lost the advantage into the lane and weakened. RIJEKA (IRE) got put in tight early then settled inside, moved closer between rivals up the backstretch, raced three deep into the far turn, stayed off the rail to the stretch and weakened. SEVENTEEN BLACK rated three then two wide early, moved out three then four deep on the backstretch, remained wide to the stretch and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANDY CAN U HEAR ME dueled for the lead from outside, took over leaving the far turn, put away GRAZED in the final sixteenth and held over the runner-up. DARK MARCUS settled inside then checked two wide on the clubhouse turn, moved closer between up the backstretch, got boxed in from the three-eighths pole to the five-sixteenths marker, found room and went between rivals around that bend, finished well through the lane but was too late. GRAZED dueled for command from inside, lost the advantage leaving the far turn, fought to the sixteenth pole and faltered late. MAXVILLE hit the gate and came away slow, trailed early on, angled six wide around the far turn, rallied widest in the lane but could not get up for third. SILENT HEAT pulled and had to steady behind the leader on the first turn, stalked up the backstretch, tipped out on the far turn and took aim three wide into the lane but failed to produce a bid. MOON ICE bumped outer rival at the start, reserved along the rail early, gained around the far turn continuing along the fence and faltered in the furlong grounds. PANTHERA'S FATE broke a step slow and got bumped leaving the gate, pulled and became rank in the early going and fought the rider all the way to the half-mile pole, came five wide into the lane and could not rally. CHIPPEWA BUD was off slow in the beginning, traveled two to three wide around both turns and also lacked a rally. HALFWAY TO NOWHERE broke a bit slow and bumped in the beginning, moved into range outside rivals, took the turn three then four wide, drifted inward in the lane and flattened. SOUL OF A WARRIOR chased along the inside into the turn, moved out to the three path around the bend and failed to rally. FULTON MARKET raced two wide near the back into the turn, remained along the two path to the stretch and made no impact. KO OLINA bobbled leaving the gate then recovered to head for the front and set the pace up the backstretch under pressure, overtaken by the winner at the five-sixteenths pole, chased two wide into the lane and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Daisycutter H. DEL MAR RACE 7 5F Turf CR: 100. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES, THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. FREE nominations close Thursday, July 20,2023 with 25 or by supplementary nomination of $1,000 each by Saturday, July 22 at noon. $100 to pass the entry box and an additional $1,500 to start, with $100,0 00 Guaranteed, of which $60,000 to first, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth and $2,000 to fifth. Weights will be issued Saturday, July 22. High weights preferred. STARTERS TO BE NAMED THROUGH THE ENTRY BOX SUNDAY, JULY 23 BY THE CLOSI NG TIME OF ENTRIES. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMY C (GB) was off slow and brushed leaving the gate, steered down to the inside, had to pause running up behind a rival into the turn, shifted to the two path around the bend, steered out in upper stretch, closed in entering the final sixteenth and bested TONY ANN late. TONY ANN sat off the pace early on, gained two wide between rivals around the bend, rallied inside the leader in deep stretch but got outclosed by the winner. PRINCESS ADALEIGH pressed the pace from outside early, failed to stay with the leader and chased while two, three, then four wide around the bend, came again entering the final sixteenth but was outkicked. SASSY NATURE set the pace under pressure from PRINCESS ADALEIGH early, cleared that rival on the turn, drifted three wide around the bend, remained clear into the final furlong, challenged by rivals on both sides with a sixteenth remaining and weakened after being overtaken. UNBRIDLED MARY chased from off the pace two wide into the turn, angled four wide around the bend, summoned a mild rally but needed to find more late. WIDE WEST (IRE) stalked the pace from inside into the turn, moved out at the top of the lane, came back in to bother rival past the eighth pole and flattened in deep stretch. TWILIGHT GLEAMING (IRE) settled inside, lacked room when boxed on the turn, gained an opening at the top of the stretch, looked to rally but was impeded by WIDE WEST (IRE) and had to take up, then could not regain momentum after. XMAS SURPRISE broke a step slow and brushed with inner rival, trailed on the inside then in the two path, moved out in the lane and failed to make an impact. SECRETS TOLD chased three wide and weakened down the lane. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY, THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED WIDE WEST (IRE) FROM SIXTH TO SEVENTH FOR CROSSING OVER AND TAKING THE PATH OF TWILIGHT GLEAMING (IRE) NEAR THE EIGHTH POLE, COSTING THAT RIVAL A CHANCE AT A BETTER PLACING.
